    "techniques/T9.005-reentrancy.md": "# Reentrancy\n\nReentrancy is a class of vulnerability where an external call into an attacker-controlled contract is made before internal accounting state is finalised. The DAO 2016 incident is the canonical historical anchor.\n\n## Indicators\n\n- repeated re-entries into the same selector before the originating call returns\n- mismatch between event-emission order and state-update order\n",
